The problem is with the conditional check. The statement `cached.active` sh
should be changed from `false` to `true` because we want to print "send", n
not "skip". Here's the corrected code:

```tundra
val cached = {
  active: true
};

val current = {
  active: true
};

if (cached.active) {
  print("send");
} else {
  print("skip");
}
```

This code will correctly print "send" when `cached.active` is true, otherwi
otherwise it will print "skip".
